Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)    get_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_multi_input_switching_mode  -  Reports the MIS (multi-input switch-
       ing) analysis settings  configured  using  the  set_multi_input_switch-
       ing_mode command

Syntax
       get_multi_input_switching_mode

       [-help]

        {[-disable_lib_cells  ]  [-switching_alignment_factor  ]  [-mis_align-
       ment_mode]}

       Reports the MIS (multi-input switching)  analysis  settings  configured
       using the set_multi_input_switching_mode command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -disable_lib_cells <string>
              Reports all the user-specified library cells for which multi-in-
              put switching (MIS) mode support is disabled.

       -mis_alignment_mode {0 | 1}
              Returns  the   current  value  set (0 or 1) of the MIS alignment
              mode.

       -switching_alignment_factor <<float>>
              Returns the switching alignment factor specified globally.

Related Information
              * set_multi_input_switching_mode

              * reportDelayCalculation

              * report_timing

              * create_spice_deck

Related Information
              * "Advanced Multiple-Input Switching Analysis"  section  in  the
                Innovus User Guide.

